    "original_notes": "TON uses a dedicated protocol family and requires TONAdapter. toncenter v2 provides both REST and JSON-RPC; response envelopes are non-standard ({ok,result,@extra}). Addresses may be raw (0:hex64), friendly bounceable (EQ...), or non-bounceable (UQ...), so adapters must normalize to raw form for de-duplication. tx_id is a tuple (account, lt, hash), not a single hash. Native decimals are 9 nanoton. Public endpoints are rate-limited to 1 RPS without an API key; production benchmarks should self-host ton-http-api.",
